oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: A loblolly pine plantation on the L. L. McMackin farm, Hollow Rock, Carroll County, planted by the Civilian Conservation Corps in 1935.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This badly eroded and gullied field, planted by the C.C.C. in 1935, has been stabilized, but heavy tramping of the area by livestock in the winter appears to have slowed the growth. Former depth of gullies shown where man stands at left center.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Administrative agencies; Forests; Pines; Soil conservation
